# Advanced Reconnaissance and OSINT

---

## **1. Core Concepts**

### ðŸ”¹ Passive Reconnaissance

* Collect intel **without directly touching the target**.
* **Techniques:** DNS enumeration, WHOIS lookups, metadata analysis.
* **Tool Example:** Shodan â€“ searches for exposed devices & services.
* **Example Query:**

  ```
  port:80 country:US
  ```

  *(Finds web servers in the United States running on port 80.)*
* **ATT\&CK Mapping:** T1595.002 â€“ Active Scanning

---

### ðŸ”¹ Active Reconnaissance

* Directly interact with the target for detailed information.
* **Techniques:** Port scanning, OS fingerprinting, service enumeration.
* **Tool Example:** Nmap
* **Example Command:**

  ```
  nmap -A -T4 <target-ip>
  ```

  *(Performs aggressive scan with OS detection & service versioning.)*
* **ATT\&CK Mapping:** T1046 â€“ Network Service Scanning

---

### ðŸ”¹ OSINT Frameworks

* **Tools:** Maltego, Recon-ng (for automated recon workflows).
* **Recon-ng Example:**

  ```
  use recon/domains-hosts/bing_domain_web
  set SOURCE example.com
  run
  ```

  *(Enumerates hosts from Bing for the target domain.)*
* **ATT\&CK Mapping:** T1593 â€“ Search Open Websites/Domains

---

## **2. Practical Exercises**

###  Shodan Search

* **Website:** [https://www.shodan.io](https://www.shodan.io)
* **Query:**

  ```
  port:80 country:US
  ```
* **Outcome:** Identified vulnerable HTTP servers exposed in the U.S.

---

### Recon-ng Domain Scan

* **Website:** [https://github.com/lanmaster53/recon-ng](https://github.com/lanmaster53/recon-ng)
* **Commands:**

  ```
  recon-ng
  marketplace install all
  use recon/domains-hosts/bing_domain_web
  set SOURCE example.com
  run
  ```
* **Outcome:** Collected subdomains & hostnames linked to the target.

---

### OSINT Framework Exploration

* **Website:** [https://osintframework.com](https://osintframework.com)
* **Activity:** Explored workflows for collecting emails, domains, and company info.

